    "result": {"pageContext":{"html":"<div class=\"table-of-contents\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#create-the-blocks\">Create the Blocks</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#configure-the-blocks\">Configure the Blocks</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#deploy-the-model-to-arduino\">Deploy the Model to Arduino</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<h2 id=\"create-the-blocks\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#create-the-blocks\" aria-label=\"create the blocks permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Create the Blocks</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 980px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/5b6b617c04cf0c85fae8fe0e1527b10d/b5cea/WeChat5b6b617c04cf0c85fae8fe0e1527b10d.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 28.9795918367347%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"links\"\n        title=\"links\"\n        src=\"/static/5b6b617c04cf0c85fae8fe0e1527b10d/d30ee/WeChat5b6b617c04cf0c85fae8fe0e1527b10d.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/5b6b617c04cf0c85fae8fe0e1527b10d/86a2e/WeChat5b6b617c04cf0c85fae8fe0e1527b10d.png 245w,\n/static/5b6b617c04cf0c85fae8fe0e1527b10d/41d3c/WeChat5b6b617c04cf0c85fae8fe0e1527b10d.png 490w,\n/static/5b6b617c04cf0c85fae8fe0e1527b10d/d30ee/WeChat5b6b617c04cf0c85fae8fe0e1527b10d.png 980w,\n/static/5b6b617c04cf0c85fae8fe0e1527b10d/b5cea/WeChat5b6b617c04cf0c85fae8fe0e1527b10d.png 1140w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 980px) 100vw, 980px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\"Sine Wave\" to simulate the speed input.</li>\n<li>\"1-D Lookup Table\" to convert the user's speed signal comming from the Sine Wave block into a PWM signal between -1 and 1.</li>\n<li>\"Gain\" block to multiplies a Simulink signal by a constant value.</li>\n<li>\"Scope\" block to visulize the output.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"configure-the-blocks\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#configure-the-blocks\" aria-label=\"configure the blocks permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Configure the Blocks</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">load motorResponse</code> to load the previous saved speedMono and PWMcmdMono</li>\n<li>We can see that the RPM is around 300. Then we configure the \"Sine Wave\" block as <code class=\"language-text\">amplitude-300, frequency-0.2</code></li>\n<li>To configure the \"1-D Lookup Table\", we set Table data to PWMcmdMono and set Breakpoints to speedMono.</li>\n<li>\"Gain\" block: Amplify the PWM duty cycle to cover a range of -100 to 100, to be compatible with the motor driver later. Double-click the Gain block and set Gain to 100. Then click OK:</li>\n<li>To access the motor connected to the Arduino Nano Motor Carrier you need an <strong>Arduino Device Driver block</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 980px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/17b17d2dd0ddeb366d1a46c6286aabd1/6f278/WeChat17b17d2dd0ddeb366d1a46c6286aabd1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 37.95918367346939%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"links-2\"\n        title=\"links-2\"\n        src=\"/static/17b17d2dd0ddeb366d1a46c6286aabd1/d30ee/WeChat17b17d2dd0ddeb366d1a46c6286aabd1.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/17b17d2dd0ddeb366d1a46c6286aabd1/86a2e/WeChat17b17d2dd0ddeb366d1a46c6286aabd1.png 245w,\n/static/17b17d2dd0ddeb366d1a46c6286aabd1/41d3c/WeChat17b17d2dd0ddeb366d1a46c6286aabd1.png 490w,\n/static/17b17d2dd0ddeb366d1a46c6286aabd1/d30ee/WeChat17b17d2dd0ddeb366d1a46c6286aabd1.png 980w,\n/static/17b17d2dd0ddeb366d1a46c6286aabd1/1134b/WeChat17b17d2dd0ddeb366d1a46c6286aabd1.png 1470w,\n/static/17b17d2dd0ddeb366d1a46c6286aabd1/6f278/WeChat17b17d2dd0ddeb366d1a46c6286aabd1.png 1488w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 980px) 100vw, 980px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2 id=\"deploy-the-model-to-arduino\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#deploy-the-model-to-arduino\" aria-label=\"deploy the model to arduino permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Deploy the Model to Arduino</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>MODELING > Model Settings:</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 980px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/eb8a1a37d6a033c12d20c7308b0d7c67/8454b/WeChateb8a1a37d6a033c12d20c7308b0d7c67.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 79.59183673469387%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"config\"\n        title=\"config\"\n        src=\"/static/eb8a1a37d6a033c12d20c7308b0d7c67/d30ee/WeChateb8a1a37d6a033c12d20c7308b0d7c67.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/eb8a1a37d6a033c12d20c7308b0d7c67/86a2e/WeChateb8a1a37d6a033c12d20c7308b0d7c67.png 245w,\n/static/eb8a1a37d6a033c12d20c7308b0d7c67/41d3c/WeChateb8a1a37d6a033c12d20c7308b0d7c67.png 490w,\n/static/eb8a1a37d6a033c12d20c7308b0d7c67/d30ee/WeChateb8a1a37d6a033c12d20c7308b0d7c67.png 980w,\n/static/eb8a1a37d6a033c12d20c7308b0d7c67/1134b/WeChateb8a1a37d6a033c12d20c7308b0d7c67.png 1470w,\n/static/eb8a1a37d6a033c12d20c7308b0d7c67/8454b/WeChateb8a1a37d6a033c12d20c7308b0d7c67.png 1798w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 980px) 100vw, 980px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Then, HARDWARE > Monitor &#x26; Tune: to build an executable and upload to hardware.</li>\n</ul>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Note: change the baud rate to 9600.</p>\n</blockquote>","date":"July 05, 2022","tags":["blog","arduino engineering kit","simulink","dc motor"],"title":"Designing a Motor Control System","description":"THIS is a note to design a motor control system that takes the users desired speed as input, following the tutorial from Arduino offical engineering kit."}},
